This decision means that there will be a trial in this case worthy of a saga on one of France's richest families, in which mother and daughter break apart while holding the realms of the empire of cosmetics L'Oréal.
But the 15th Correctional Chamber also ordered that Liliane Bettencourt's medical expertise, aged 87, should be carried out collegially by three doctors.
L'Oréal's principal heir and shareholder has always refused to undergo such an examination, in any case not under the conditions proposed by the Nanterre Prosecutor's Office during the investigation.
