It is an excellent news (...) Expertise will demonstrate that he (Mr. Banier) manipulated this elderly lady that we must protect, he said.
For the past two years, Liliane Bettencourt's single daughter has been prosecuting François-Marie Banier, a photographer and artist, who has been accused of taking advantage of her mother's weakness for years to obtain one billion euros of gifts, in the form of cheques, life insurance contracts or master's tables.
For her part, Liliane Bettencourt has always refused to have been manipulated by the photographer, whom she considers to be a long-standing friend.
While the court had to examine the admissibility of the action undertaken by Ms. Bettencourt-Meyers, lawyers' pleadings sometimes turned to the big family play on Friday.
